SIMPLE: maintain
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Maintain
<hw>Main*tain</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Maintained</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Maintaining</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>maintenen</ets>, F. <ets>maintenir</ets>, properly, to hold by the
hand; <ets>main</ets> hand (L. <ets>manus</ets>) + F. <ets>tenir</ets>
to hold (L. <ets>tenere</ets>). See <er>Manual</er>, and Tenable.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To hold or keep in any particular state or condition;
to support; to sustain; to uphold; to keep up; not to suffer to fail or
decline; <as>as, to <ex>maintain</ex> a certain degree of heat in a
furnace; to <ex>maintain</ex> a fence or a railroad; to
<ex>maintain</ex> the digestive process or powers of the stomach; to
<ex>maintain</ex> the fertility of soil; to <ex>maintain</ex> present
reputation.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To keep possession of; to hold and defend; not to
surrender or relinquish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God values . . . every one as he <qex>maintains</qex> his
post.</q> <rj><qau>Grew.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To continue; not to suffer to cease or
fail.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Maintain</qex> talk with the duke.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To bear the expense of; to support; to keep up; to
supply with what is needed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Glad, by his labor, to <qex>maintain</qex> his life.</q>
<rj><qau>Stirling.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What <qex>maintains</qex> one vice would bring up two
children.</q> <rj><qau>Franklin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>To affirm; to support or defend by
argument.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is hard to <qex>maintain</qex> the truth, but much harder to be
maintained by it.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To assert; vindicate; allege. See
<er>Assert</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maintainable</ent>⟦br⟧
